The City of Cape Town's Fire and Rescue Service spokesperson, Jermaine Carelse gives an update on the fire on Table Mountain. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Firefighters have contained the fire on Table Mountain. The blaze which was fanned by strong winds began on Saturday and continued into the early hours of Sunday morning. READ: Firefighters battle blaze on Table Mountain Cape Town Fire and Rescue spokesperson, Jermaine Carelse, says they will continue monitoring the situation. "We are going to monitor the area for hotspots and any flare-ups during the day," Carelse said. "But luckily the wind has subsided and we are having a beautiful day in Cape Town, there is no wind currently but it looks like the wind will pick up at around 5pm tonight but by that time, the fire would have been extinguished properly."